4988 offset = dissect_dcerpc_uint32(tvb, offset, pinfo, cn_rts_command_tree, hdr->drep, hf_dcerpc_cn_rts_command_connectiontimeout, NULL((void*)0));
4989 break;
4990 case RTS_CMD_COOKIE0x3:
4991 offset = dissect_dcerpc_uuid_t(tvb, offset, pinfo, cn_rts_command_tree, hdr->drep, hf_dcerpc_cn_rts_command_cookie, NULL((void*)0));
4992 break;
4993 case RTS_CMD_CHANNELLIFETIME0x4:
4994 offset = dissect_dcerpc_uint32(tvb, offset, pinfo, cn_rts_command_tree, hdr->drep, hf_dcerpc_cn_rts_command_channellifetime, NULL((void*)0));
4995 break;
4996 case RTS_CMD_CLIENTKEEPALIVE0x5:
4997 offset = dissect_dcerpc_uint32(tvb, offset, pinfo, cn_rts_command_tree, hdr->drep, hf_dcerpc_cn_rts_command_clientkeepalive, NULL((void*)0));
4998 break;
4999 case RTS_CMD_VERSION0x6:
5000 offset = dissect_dcerpc_uint32(tvb, offset, pinfo, cn_rts_command_tree, hdr->drep, hf_dcerpc_cn_rts_command_version, NULL((void*)0));
5001 break;
5002 case RTS_CMD_EMPTY0x7:
5003 break;
5004 case RTS_CMD_PADDING0x8: {
5005 guint8 *padding;
5006 const guint32 conformance_count = dcerpc_tvb_get_ntohl(tvb, offset, hdr->drep);
5007 proto_tree_add_uint(cn_rts_command_tree, hf_dcerpc_cn_rts_command_conformancecount, tvb, offset, 4, conformance_count);
5008 offset += 4;
5009 padding = (guint8 *)tvb_memdup(wmem_packet_scope(), tvb, offset, conformance_count);
5010 proto_tree_add_bytes(cn_rts_command_tree, hf_dcerpc_cn_rts_command_padding, tvb, offset, conformance_count, padding);
5011 offset += conformance_count;
5012 } break;
5013 case RTS_CMD_NEGATIVEANCE0x9:
5014 break;
5015 case RTS_CMD_ANCE0xA:
5016 break;
5017 case RTS_CMD_CLIENTADDRESS0xB: {
5018 guint8 *padding;
5019 const guint32 addrtype = dcerpc_tvb_get_ntohl(tvb, offset, hdr->drep);
5020 proto_tree_add_uint(cn_rts_command_tree, hf_dcerpc_cn_rts_command_addrtype, tvb, offset, 4, addrtype);
5021 offset += 4;
5022 switch (addrtype) {
5023 case RTS_IPV40: {
5024 const guint32 addr4 = tvb_get_ipv4(tvb, offset);
5025 proto_tree_add_ipv4_format_value(cn_rts_command_tree, hf_dcerpc_cmd_client_ipv4, tvb, offset, 4, addr4, "%s", get_hostname(addr4));
5026 offset += 4;
5027 } break;
5028 case RTS_IPV61: {
5029 struct e_in6_addr addr6;
5030 tvb_get_ipv6(tvb, offset, &addr6);
5031 proto_tree_add_ipv6_format_value(cn_rts_command_tree, hf_dcerpc_cmd_client_ipv6, tvb, offset, 16, &addr6, "%s", get_hostname6(&addr6));
5032 offset += 16;
5033 } break;
5034 }
5035 padding = (guint8 *)tvb_memdup(wmem_packet_scope(), tvb, offset, 12);
5036 proto_tree_add_bytes(cn_rts_command_tree, hf_dcerpc_cn_rts_command_padding, tvb, offset, 12, padding);
5037 offset += 12;
5038 } break;
5039 case RTS_CMD_ASSOCIATIONGROUPID0xC:
5040 offset = dissect_dcerpc_uuid_t(tvb, offset, pinfo, cn_rts_command_tree, hdr->drep, hf_dcerpc_cn_rts_command_associationgroupid, NULL((void*)0));
5041 break;
5042 case RTS_CMD_DESTINATION0xD:
5043 offset = dissect_dcerpc_uint32(tvb, offset, pinfo, cn_rts_command_tree, hdr->drep, hf_dcerpc_cn_rts_command_forwarddestination, NULL((void*)0));
5044 break;
5045 case RTS_CMD_PINGTRAFFICSENTNOTIFY0xE:
5046 offset = dissect_dcerpc_uint32(tvb, offset, pinfo, cn_rts_command_tree, hdr->drep, hf_dcerpc_cn_rts_command_pingtrafficsentnotify, NULL((void*)0));
5047 break;
5048 default:
5049 expert_add_info(pinfo, tf, &ei_dcerpc_cn_rts_command);
5050 break;
5051 }
5052 }
5053
5054 col_set_str(pinfo->cinfo, COL_PROTOCOL, "RPCH");
5055
5056 /* Define which PDU Body we are dealing with */
5057 info_str = "unknown RTS PDU";
5058
5059 switch (rts_flags) {
5060 case RTS_FLAG_NONE0x0000:
5061 switch (commands_nb) {
5062 case 1:
5063 if (cmd[0] == 0x2) {
5064 info_str = "CONN/A3";
5065 } else if (cmd[0] == 0x3) {
5066 info_str = "IN_R1/A5,IN_R1/A6,IN_R2/A2,IN_R2/A5,OUT_R2/A4";
5067 } else if (cmd[0] == 0x7) {
5068 info_str = "IN_R1/B1";
5069 } else if (cmd[0] == 0x0) {
5070 info_str = "IN_R1/B2";
5071 } else if (cmd[0] == 0xD) {
5072 info_str = "IN_R2/A3,IN_R2/A4";
5073 } else if (cmd[0] == 0xA) {
5074 info_str = "OUT_R1/A9,OUT_R1/A10,OUT_R1/A11,OUT_R2/B1,OUT_R2/B2";
5075 }
5076 break;
5077 case 2:
5078 if ((cmd[0] == 0x0) && (cmd[1] == 0x6)) {
5079 info_str = "CONN/B3";
5080 } else if ((cmd[0] == 0xD) && (cmd[1] == 0xA)) {
5081 info_str = "OUT_R2/A5,OUT_R2/A6";
5082 }
5083 break;
5084 case 3:
5085 if ((cmd[0] == 0x6) && (cmd[1] == 0x0) && (cmd[2] == 0x2)) {
5086 info_str = "CONN/C1,CONN/C2";
5087 }
5088 break;
5089 case 4:
5090 if ((cmd[0] == 0x6) && (cmd[1] == 0x3) && (cmd[2] == 0x3) && (cmd[3] == 0x0)) {
5091 info_str = "CONN/A1";
5092 } else if ((cmd[0] == 0xD) && (cmd[1] == 0x6) && (cmd[2] == 0x0) && (cmd[3] == 0x2)) {
5093 info_str = "IN_R1/A3,IN_R1/A4";
5094 }
5095 break;
5096 case 6:
5097 if ((cmd[0] == 0x6) && (cmd[1] == 0x3) && (cmd[2] == 0x3) && (cmd[3] == 0x4) && (cmd[4] == 0x5) && (cmd[5] == 0xC)) {
5098 info_str = "CONN/B1";
5099 }
5100 break;
5101 default:
5102 break;
5103 }
5104 break;
5105 case RTS_FLAG_PING0x0001:
5106 switch (commands_nb) {
5107 case 0:
5108 info_str = "Ping";
5109 break;
5110 case 1:
5111 if ((cmd[0] == 0x7) || (cmd[0] == 0x8)) {
5112 info_str = "OUT_R2/C1";
5113 }
5114 break;
5115 default:
5116 break;
5117 }
5118 break;
5119 case RTS_FLAG_OTHER_CMD0x0002:
5120 switch (commands_nb) {
5121 case 1:
5122 if (cmd[0] == 0x5) {
5123 info_str = "Keep-Alive";
5124 } else if (cmd[0] == 0xE) {
5125 info_str = "PingTrafficSentNotify";
5126 } else if (cmd[0] == 0x1) {
5127 info_str = "FlowControlAck";
5128 }
5129 break;
5130 case 2:
5131 if ((cmd[0] == 0xD) && (cmd[1] == 0x1)) {
5132 info_str = "FlowControlAckWithDestination";
5133 }
5134 break;
5135 default:
5136 break;
5137 }
5138 break;
5139 case RTS_FLAG_RECYCLE_CHANNEL0x0004:
5140 switch (commands_nb) {
5141 case 1:
5142 if (cmd[0] == 0xD) {
5143 info_str = "OUT_R1/A1,OUT_R1/A2,OUT_R2/A1,OUT_R2/A2";
5144 }
5145 break;
5146 case 4:
5147 if ((cmd[0] == 0x6) && (cmd[1] == 0x3) && (cmd[2] == 0x3) && (cmd[3] == 0x3)) {
5148 info_str = "IN_R1/A1,IN_R2/A1";
5149 }
5150 break;
5151 case 5:
5152 if ((cmd[0] == 0x6) && (cmd[1] == 0x3) && (cmd[2] == 0x3) && (cmd[3] == 0x3) && (cmd[4] == 0x0)) {
5153 info_str = "OUT_R1/A3,OUT_R2/A3";
5154 }
5155 break;
5156 default:
5157 break;
5158 }
5159 break;
5160 case RTS_FLAG_IN_CHANNEL0x0008|RTS_FLAG_RECYCLE_CHANNEL0x0004:
5161 switch (commands_nb) {
5162 case 6:
5163 if ((cmd[0] == 0x6) && (cmd[1] == 0x3) && (cmd[2] == 0x3) && (cmd[3] == 0x3) && (cmd[4] == 0x0) && (cmd[5] == 0x2)) {
5164 info_str = "IN_R1/A2";
5165 }
5166 break;
5167 default:
5168 break;
5169 }
5170 break;
5171 case RTS_FLAG_IN_CHANNEL0x0008:
5172 switch (commands_nb) {
5173 case 7:
5174 if ((cmd[0] == 0x6) && (cmd[1] == 0x3) && (cmd[2] == 0x3) && (cmd[3] == 0x0) && (cmd[4] == 0x2) && (cmd[5] == 0xC) && (cmd[6] == 0xB)) {
5175 info_str = "CONN/B2";
5176 }
5177 break;
5178 default:
5179 break;
5180 }
5181 break;
5182 case RTS_FLAG_OUT_CHANNEL0x0010|RTS_FLAG_RECYCLE_CHANNEL0x0004:
5183 switch (commands_nb) {
5184 case 7:
5185 if ((cmd[0] == 0x6) && (cmd[1] == 0x3) && (cmd[2] == 0x3) && (cmd[3] == 0x3) && (cmd[4] == 0x4) && (cmd[5] == 0) && (cmd[6] == 0x2)) {
5186 info_str = "OUT_R1/A4";
5187 }
5188 break;
5189 default:
5190 break;
5191 }
5192 break;
5193 case RTS_FLAG_OUT_CHANNEL0x0010:
5194 switch (commands_nb) {
5195 case 2:
5196 if ((cmd[0] == 0xD) && (cmd[1] == 0x3)) {
5197 info_str = "OUT_R1/A7,OUT_R1/A8,OUT_R2/A8";
5198 }
5199 break;
5200 case 3:
5201 if ((cmd[0] == 0xD) && (cmd[1] == 0x6) && (cmd[2] == 0x2)) {
5202 info_str = "OUT_R1/A5,OUT_R1/A6";
5203 } else if ((cmd[0] == 0xD) && (cmd[1] == 0x3) && (cmd[2] == 0x6)) {
5204 info_str = "OUT_R2/A7";
5205 }
5206 break;
5207 case 5:
5208 if ((cmd[0] == 0x6) && (cmd[1] == 0x3) && (cmd[2] == 0x3) && (cmd[3] == 0x4) && (cmd[4] == 0x0)) {
5209 info_str = "CONN/A2";
5210 }
5211 break;
5212 default:
5213 break;
5214 }
5215 break;
5216 case RTS_FLAG_EOF0x0020:
5217 switch (commands_nb) {
5218 case 1:
5219 if (cmd[0] == 0xA) {
5220 info_str = "OUT_R2/B3";
5221 }
5222 break;
5223 default:
5224 break;
5225 }
5226 break;
5227 case RTS_FLAG_ECHO0x0040:
5228 switch (commands_nb) {
5229 case 0:
5230 info_str = "Echo";
5231 break;
5232 default:
5233 break;
5234 }
5235 break;
5236 default:
5237 break;
5238 }
5239
5240 col_add_fstr(pinfo->cinfo, COL_INFO, "%s, ", info_str);
5241 col_set_fence(pinfo->cinfo,COL_INFO);
5242
5243 parent_pi = proto_tree_get_parent(dcerpc_tree);
5244 if (parent_pi != NULL((void*)0)) {
5245 proto_item_append_text(parent_pi, ", %s", info_str);
5246 }
5247}
5248
5249static gboolean
5250is_dcerpc(tvbuff_t *tvb, int offset, packet_info *pinfo _U___attribute__((unused)))
5251{
5252 guint8 rpc_ver;
5253 guint8 rpc_ver_minor;
5254 guint8 ptype;
5255
5256 if (!tvb_bytes_exist(tvb, offset, sizeof(e_dce_cn_common_hdr_t)))
5257 return FALSE(0); /* not enough information to check */
5258
5259 rpc_ver = tvb_get_guint8(tvb, offset++);
5260 if (rpc_ver != 5)
5261 return FALSE(0);
5262 rpc_ver_minor = tvb_get_guint8(tvb, offset++);
5263 if ((rpc_ver_minor != 0) && (rpc_ver_minor != 1))
5264 return FALSE(0);
5265 ptype = tvb_get_guint8(tvb, offset++);
5266 if (ptype > PDU_RTS20)
5267 return FALSE(0);
5268
5269 return TRUE(!(0));
5270}
5271
5272/*
5273 * DCERPC dissector for connection oriented calls.
5274 */
5275static gboolean
5276dissect_dcerpc_cn(tvbuff_t *tvb, int offset, packet_info *pinfo,
5277 proto_tree *tree, gboolean can_desegment, int *pkt_len)
5278{
5279 static const guint8 nulls[4] = { 0 };
5280 int start_offset;
5281 int padding = 0;
5282 int subtvb_len = 0;
5283 proto_item *ti = NULL((void*)0);
5284 proto_item *tf = NULL((void*)0);
5285 proto_tree *dcerpc_tree = NULL((void*)0);
5286 e_dce_cn_common_hdr_t hdr;
5287 dcerpc_auth_info auth_info;
5288 tvbuff_t *fragment_tvb;
5289 dcerpc_decode_as_data* decode_data = dcerpc_get_decode_data(pinfo);
5290 static const int * hdr_flags[] = {
5291 &hf_dcerpc_cn_flags_object,
5292 &hf_dcerpc_cn_flags_maybe,
5293 &hf_dcerpc_cn_flags_dne,
5294 &hf_dcerpc_cn_flags_mpx,
5295 &hf_dcerpc_cn_flags_reserved,
5296 &hf_dcerpc_cn_flags_cancel_pending,
5297 &hf_dcerpc_cn_flags_last_frag,
5298 &hf_dcerpc_cn_flags_first_frag,
5299 NULL((void*)0)
5300 };
5301
5302 /*
5303 * when done over nbt, dcerpc requests are padded with 4 bytes of null
5304 * data for some reason.
5305 *
5306 * XXX - if that's always the case, the right way to do this would
5307 * be to have a "dissect_dcerpc_cn_nb" routine which strips off
5308 * the 4 bytes of null padding, and make that the dissector
5309 * used for "netbios".
5310 */
5311 if (tvb_memeql(tvb, offset, nulls, 4) == 0) {
5312
5313 /*
5314 * Skip the padding.
5315 */
5316 offset += 4;
5317 padding += 4;
5318 }
5319 /*
5320 * Check if this looks like a C/O DCERPC call
5321 */
5322 if (!is_dcerpc(tvb, offset, pinfo))
5323 return FALSE(0);
5324
5325 start_offset = offset;
5326 hdr.rpc_ver = tvb_get_guint8(tvb, offset++);
5327 hdr.rpc_ver_minor = tvb_get_guint8(tvb, offset++);
5328 hdr.ptype = tvb_get_guint8(tvb, offset++);
5329
5330 hdr.flags = tvb_get_guint8(tvb, offset++);
5331 tvb_memcpy(tvb, (guint8 *)hdr.drep, offset, sizeof (hdr.drep));
5332 offset += (int)sizeof (hdr.drep);
5333
5334 hdr.frag_len = dcerpc_tvb_get_ntohs(tvb, offset, hdr.drep);
5335 offset += 2;
5336 hdr.auth_len = dcerpc_tvb_get_ntohs(tvb, offset, hdr.drep);
5337 offset += 2;
5338 hdr.call_id = dcerpc_tvb_get_ntohl(tvb, offset, hdr.drep);
5339 /*offset += 4;*/
5340
5341 if (decode_data->dcectxid == 0) {
5342 col_append_fstr(pinfo->cinfo, COL_DCE_CALL, "%u", hdr.call_id);
5343 } else {
5344 /* this is not the first DCE-RPC request/response in this (TCP?-)PDU,
5345 * prepend a delimiter */
5346 col_append_fstr(pinfo->cinfo, COL_DCE_CALL, "#%u", hdr.call_id);
5347 }
5348
5349 if (can_desegment && pinfo->can_desegment
5350 && !tvb_bytes_exist(tvb, start_offset, hdr.frag_len)) {
5351 pinfo->desegment_offset = start_offset;
5352 pinfo->desegment_len = hdr.frag_len - tvb_reported_length_remaining(tvb, start_offset);
5353 *pkt_len = 0; /* desegmentation required */
5354 return TRUE(!(0));
5355 }
5356
5357 col_set_str(pinfo->cinfo, COL_PROTOCOL, "DCERPC");
5358
5359 if (decode_data->dcectxid != 0) {
5360 /* this is not the first DCE-RPC request/response in this (TCP?-)PDU,
5361 * append a delimiter and set a column fence */
5362 col_append_str(pinfo->cinfo, COL_INFO, " # ");
5363 col_set_fence(pinfo->cinfo,COL_INFO);
5364 }
5365 col_add_fstr(pinfo->cinfo, COL_INFO, "%s: call_id: %u",
5366 pckt_vals[hdr.ptype].strptr, hdr.call_id);
5367
5368 if (decode_data->dcectxid != 0) {
5369 /* this is not the first DCE-RPC request/response in this (TCP?-)PDU */
5370 expert_add_info(pinfo, NULL((void*)0), &ei_dcerpc_fragment_multiple);
5371 }
5372
5373 offset = start_offset;
5374 tvb_ensure_bytes_exist(tvb, offset, 16);
5375 if (tree) {
5376 ti = proto_tree_add_item(tree, proto_dcerpc, tvb, offset, hdr.frag_len, ENC_NA0x00000000);
5377 dcerpc_tree = proto_item_add_subtree(ti, ett_dcerpc);
5378 }
5379
5380 proto_tree_add_uint(dcerpc_tree, hf_dcerpc_ver, tvb, offset, 1, hdr.rpc_ver);
5381 offset++;
5382
5383 proto_tree_add_uint(dcerpc_tree, hf_dcerpc_ver_minor, tvb, offset, 1, hdr.rpc_ver_minor);
5384 offset++;
5385
5386 tf = proto_tree_add_uint(dcerpc_tree, hf_dcerpc_packet_type, tvb, offset, 1, hdr.ptype);
5387 offset++;
5388
5389#if 0 /* XXX - too much "output noise", removed for now */
5390 if (hdr.ptype == PDU_BIND11 || hdr.ptype == PDU_ALTER14 ||
5391 hdr.ptype == PDU_BIND_ACK12 || hdr.ptype == PDU_ALTER_ACK15)
5392 expert_add_info_format(pinfo, tf, &ei_dcerpc_context_change, "Context change: %s", val_to_str(hdr.ptype, pckt_vals, "(0x%x)"));
5393#endif
5394 if (hdr.ptype == PDU_BIND_NAK13)
5395 expert_add_info(pinfo, tf, &ei_dcerpc_bind_not_acknowledged);
5396
5397 if (tree) {
5398 proto_item_append_text(ti, " %s, Fragment: %s",
5399 val_to_str(hdr.ptype, pckt_vals, "Unknown (0x%02x)"),
5400 fragment_type(hdr.flags));
5401 }
5402
5403 proto_tree_add_bitmask_value_with_flags(dcerpc_tree, tvb, offset, hf_dcerpc_cn_flags,
5404 ett_dcerpc_cn_flags, hdr_flags, hdr.flags, BMT_NO_APPEND0x01);
5405 offset++;
5406
5407 col_append_fstr(pinfo->cinfo, COL_INFO, ", Fragment: %s", fragment_type(hdr.flags));
5408
5409 proto_tree_add_dcerpc_drep(dcerpc_tree, tvb, offset, hdr.drep, (int)sizeof (hdr.drep));
5410 offset += (int)sizeof (hdr.drep);
5411
5412 proto_tree_add_uint(dcerpc_tree, hf_dcerpc_cn_frag_len, tvb, offset, 2, hdr.frag_len);
5413 offset += 2;
5414
5415 proto_tree_add_uint(dcerpc_tree, hf_dcerpc_cn_auth_len, tvb, offset, 2, hdr.auth_len);
5416 offset += 2;
5417
5418 proto_tree_add_uint(dcerpc_tree, hf_dcerpc_cn_call_id, tvb, offset, 4, hdr.call_id);
5419 offset += 4;
5420
5421 if (ti) {
5422 proto_item_append_text(ti, ", FragLen: %u, Call: %u", hdr.frag_len, hdr.call_id);
5423 }
5424
5425 /*
5426 * None of the stuff done above should throw an exception, because
5427 * we would have rejected this as "not DCE RPC" if we didn't have all
5428 * of it. (XXX - perhaps we should request reassembly if we have
5429 * enough of the header to consider it DCE RPC but not enough to
5430 * get the fragment length; in that case the stuff still wouldn't
5431 * throw an exception.)
5432 *
5433 * The rest of the stuff might, so return the PDU length to our caller.
5434 * XXX - should we construct a tvbuff containing only the PDU and
5435 * use that? Or should we have separate "is this a DCE RPC PDU",
5436 * "how long is it", and "dissect it" routines - which might let us
5437 * do most of the work in "tcp_dissect_pdus()"?
5438 */
5439 if (pkt_len != NULL((void*)0))
5440 *pkt_len = hdr.frag_len + padding;
5441
5442 /* The remaining bytes in the current tvb might contain multiple
5443 * DCE/RPC fragments, so create a new tvb subset for this fragment.
5444 * Only limit the end of the fragment, but not the offset start,
5445 * as the authentication function dissect_dcerpc_cn_auth() will fail
5446 * (and other functions might fail as well) computing the right start
5447 * offset otherwise.
5448 */
5449 subtvb_len = MIN(hdr.frag_len, tvb_reported_length(tvb))(((hdr.frag_len) < (tvb_reported_length(tvb))) ? (hdr.frag_len
) : (tvb_reported_length(tvb)));
5450 fragment_tvb = tvb_new_subset(tvb, start_offset,
5451 subtvb_len /* length */,
5452 hdr.frag_len /* reported_length */);
5453
5454 /*
5455 * Packet type specific stuff is next.
5456 */
5457 switch (hdr.ptype) {
5458 case PDU_BIND11:
5459 case PDU_ALTER14:
5460 dissect_dcerpc_cn_bind(fragment_tvb, MIN(offset - start_offset, subtvb_len)(((offset - start_offset) < (subtvb_len)) ? (offset - start_offset
) : (subtvb_len)), pinfo, dcerpc_tree, &hdr);
5461 break;
5462
5463 case PDU_BIND_ACK12:
5464 case PDU_ALTER_ACK15:
5465 dissect_dcerpc_cn_bind_ack(fragment_tvb, MIN(offset - start_offset, subtvb_len)(((offset - start_offset) < (subtvb_len)) ? (offset - start_offset
) : (subtvb_len)), pinfo, dcerpc_tree, &hdr);
5466 break;
5467
5468 case PDU_AUTH316:
5469 /*
5470 * Nothing after the common header other than credentials.
5471 */
5472 dissect_dcerpc_cn_auth(fragment_tvb, MIN(offset - start_offset, subtvb_len)(((offset - start_offset) < (subtvb_len)) ? (offset - start_offset
) : (subtvb_len)), pinfo, dcerpc_tree, &hdr, TRUE(!(0)),
5473 &auth_info);
5474 break;
5475
5476 case PDU_REQ0:
5477 dissect_dcerpc_cn_rqst(fragment_tvb, MIN(offset - start_offset, subtvb_len)(((offset - start_offset) < (subtvb_len)) ? (offset - start_offset
) : (subtvb_len)), pinfo, dcerpc_tree, tree, &hdr);
5478 break;
5479
5480 case PDU_RESP2:
5481 dissect_dcerpc_cn_resp(fragment_tvb, MIN(offset - start_offset, subtvb_len)(((offset - start_offset) < (subtvb_len)) ? (offset - start_offset
) : (subtvb_len)), pinfo, dcerpc_tree, tree, &hdr);
5482 break;
5483
5484 case PDU_FAULT3:
5485 dissect_dcerpc_cn_fault(fragment_tvb, MIN(offset - start_offset, subtvb_len)(((offset - start_offset) < (subtvb_len)) ? (offset - start_offset
) : (subtvb_len)), pinfo, dcerpc_tree, &hdr);
5486 break;
5487
5488 case PDU_BIND_NAK13:
5489 dissect_dcerpc_cn_bind_nak(fragment_tvb, MIN(offset - start_offset, subtvb_len)(((offset - start_offset) < (subtvb_len)) ? (offset - start_offset
) : (subtvb_len)), pinfo, dcerpc_tree, &hdr);
5490 break;
5491
5492 case PDU_CO_CANCEL18:
5493 case PDU_ORPHANED19:
5494 /*
5495 * Nothing after the common header other than an authentication
5496 * verifier.
5497 */
5498 dissect_dcerpc_cn_auth(fragment_tvb, MIN(offset - start_offset, subtvb_len)(((offset - start_offset) < (subtvb_len)) ? (offset - start_offset
) : (subtvb_len)), pinfo, dcerpc_tree, &hdr, FALSE(0),
5499 &auth_info);
5500 break;
5501
5502 case PDU_SHUTDOWN17:
5503 /*
5504 * Nothing after the common header, not even an authentication
5505 * verifier.
5506 */
5507 break;
5508 case PDU_RTS20:
5509 dissect_dcerpc_cn_rts(fragment_tvb, MIN(offset - start_offset, subtvb_len)(((offset - start_offset) < (subtvb_len)) ? (offset - start_offset
) : (subtvb_len)), pinfo, dcerpc_tree, &hdr);
5510 break;
5511
5512 default:
5513 /* might as well dissect the auth info */
5514 dissect_dcerpc_cn_auth(fragment_tvb, MIN(offset - start_offset, subtvb_len)(((offset - start_offset) < (subtvb_len)) ? (offset - start_offset
) : (subtvb_len)), pinfo, dcerpc_tree, &hdr, FALSE(0),
5515 &auth_info);
5516 break;
5517 }
5518 return TRUE(!(0));
5519}
5520
5521/*
5522 * DCERPC dissector for connection oriented calls over packet-oriented
5523 * transports
5524 */
5525static gboolean
5526dissect_dcerpc_cn_pk(tvbuff_t *tvb, packet_info *pinfo, proto_tree *tree, void *data _U___attribute__((unused)))
5527{
5528 dcerpc_decode_as_data* decode_data = dcerpc_get_decode_data(pinfo);
5529
5530 /*
5531 * Only one PDU per transport packet, and only one transport
5532 * packet per PDU.
5533 */
5534 decode_data->dcetransporttype = DCE_TRANSPORT_UNKNOWN0;
5535 if (!dissect_dcerpc_cn(tvb, 0, pinfo, tree, FALSE(0), NULL((void*)0))) {
5536 /*
5537 * It wasn't a DCERPC PDU.
5538 */
5539 return FALSE(0);
5540 } else {
5541 /*
5542 * It was.
5543 */
5544 return TRUE(!(0));
5545 }
5546}
5547
5548/*
5549 * DCERPC dissector for connection oriented calls over byte-stream
5550 * transports.
5551 * we need to distinguish here between SMB and non-TCP (more in the future?)
5552 * to be able to know what kind of private_data structure to expect.
5553 */
5554static gboolean
5555dissect_dcerpc_cn_bs_body(tvbuff_t *tvb, packet_info *pinfo, proto_tree *tree)
5556{
5557 volatile int offset = 0;
5558 int pdu_len = 0;
5559 volatile int dcerpc_pdus = 0;
5560 volatile gboolean ret = FALSE(0);
5561
5562 /*
5563 * There may be multiple PDUs per transport packet; keep
5564 * processing them.
5565 */
5566 while (tvb_reported_length_remaining(tvb, offset) != 0) {
5567 TRY{ except_t *volatile exc; volatile int except_state = 0; static
const except_id_t catch_spec[] = { { 1, 0 } }; { struct except_stacknode
except_sn; struct except_catch except_ch; except_setup_try(&
except_sn, &except_ch, catch_spec, 1); if (_setjmp (except_ch
.except_jmp)) *(&exc) = &except_ch.except_obj; else *
(&exc) = 0; if(except_state & 1) except_state |= 2; except_state
&= ~1; if (except_state == 0 && exc == 0) {
5568 pdu_len = 0;
5569 if (dissect_dcerpc_cn(tvb, offset, pinfo, tree,
5570 dcerpc_cn_desegment, &pdu_len)) {
5571 dcerpc_pdus++;
5572 }
5573 } CATCH_NONFATAL_ERRORSif (except_state == 0 && exc != 0 && (exc->
except_id.except_code == (2) || exc->except_id.except_code
== (6) || exc->except_id.except_code == (8)) && (
except_state|=1)) {
5574 /*
5575 * Somebody threw an exception that means that there
5576 * was a problem dissecting the payload; that means
5577 * that a dissector was found, so we don't need to
5578 * dissect the payload as data or update the protocol
5579 * or info columns.
5580 *
5581 * Just show the exception and then continue dissecting
5582 * PDUs.
5583 */
5584 show_exception(tvb, pinfo, tree, EXCEPT_CODE((exc)->except_id.except_code), GET_MESSAGE((exc)->except_message));
5585 /*
5586 * Presumably it looked enough like a DCE RPC PDU that we
5587 * dissected enough of it to throw an exception.
5588 */
5589 dcerpc_pdus++;
5590 } ENDTRYif(!(except_state&1) && exc != 0) except_rethrow(
exc); except_free(except_ch.except_obj.except_dyndata); except_pop
(); };};
5591
5592 if (dcerpc_pdus == 0) {
5593 gboolean try_desegment = FALSE(0);
5594 if (dcerpc_cn_desegment && pinfo->can_desegment &&
5595 !tvb_bytes_exist(tvb, offset, sizeof(e_dce_cn_common_hdr_t))) {
5596 /* look for a previous occurrence of the DCE-RPC protocol */
5597 wmem_list_frame_t *cur;
5598 cur = wmem_list_frame_prev(wmem_list_tail(pinfo->layers));
5599 while (cur != NULL((void*)0)) {
5600 if (proto_dcerpc == (gint)GPOINTER_TO_UINT(wmem_list_frame_data(cur))((guint) (gulong) (wmem_list_frame_data(cur)))) {
5601 try_desegment = TRUE(!(0));
5602 break;
5603 }
5604 cur = wmem_list_frame_prev(cur);
5605 }
5606 }
5607
5608 if (try_desegment) {
5609 /* It didn't look like DCE-RPC but we already had one DCE-RPC
5610 * layer in this packet and what we have is short. Assume that
5611 * it was just too short to tell and ask the TCP layer for more
5612 * data. */
5613 pinfo->desegment_offset = offset;
5614 pinfo->desegment_len = (guint32)(sizeof(e_dce_cn_common_hdr_t) - tvb_reported_length_remaining(tvb, offset));
5615 } else {
5616 /* Really not DCE-RPC */
5617 break;
5618 }
5619 }
5620
5621 /*
5622 * Well, we've seen at least one DCERPC PDU.
5623 */
5624 ret = TRUE(!(0));
5625
5626 /* if we had more than one Req/Resp in this PDU change the protocol column */
5627 /* this will formerly contain the last interface name, which may not be the same for all Req/Resp */
5628 if (dcerpc_pdus >= 2)
5629 col_add_fstr(pinfo->cinfo, COL_PROTOCOL, "%u*DCERPC", dcerpc_pdus);
5630
5631 if (pdu_len == 0) {
5632 /*
5633 * Desegmentation required - bail now, but give the user a hint that desegmentation might be done later.
5634 */
5635 proto_tree_add_uint_format(tree, hf_dcerpc_cn_deseg_req, tvb, offset,
5636 0,
5637 tvb_reported_length_remaining(tvb, offset),
5638 "[DCE RPC: %u byte%s left, desegmentation might follow]",
5639 tvb_reported_length_remaining(tvb, offset),
5640 plurality(tvb_reported_length_remaining(tvb, offset), "", "s")((tvb_reported_length_remaining(tvb, offset)) == 1 ? ("") : (
"s")));
5641 break;
5642 }
5643
5644 /*
5645 * Step to the next PDU.
5646 */
5647 offset += pdu_len;
5648 }
5649 return ret;
5650}
5651
5652static gboolean
5653dissect_dcerpc_cn_bs(tvbuff_t *tvb, packet_info *pinfo, proto_tree *tree, void *data _U___attribute__((unused)))
5654{
5655 dcerpc_decode_as_data* decode_data = dcerpc_get_decode_data(pinfo);
5656
5657 decode_data->dcetransporttype = DCE_TRANSPORT_UNKNOWN0;
5658 return dissect_dcerpc_cn_bs_body(tvb, pinfo, tree);
5659}
5660
5661static guint
5662get_dcerpc_pdu_len(packet_info *pinfo _U___attribute__((unused)), tvbuff_t *tvb,
5663 int offset _U___attribute__((unused)), void *data _U___attribute__((unused)))
5664{
5665 guint8 drep[4];
5666 guint16 frag_len;
5667
5668 /* XXX: why does htis not take offset into account? */
5669 tvb_memcpy(tvb, (guint8 *)drep, 4, sizeof(drep));
5670 frag_len = dcerpc_tvb_get_ntohs(tvb, 8, drep);
5671
5672 return frag_len;
5673}
5674
5675static int
5676dissect_dcerpc_pdu(tvbuff_t *tvb, packet_info *pinfo, proto_tree *tree, void* data _U___attribute__((unused)))
5677{
5678 int pdu_len = 0;
5679 dissect_dcerpc_cn(tvb, 0, pinfo, tree,
5680 /* Desegment is already handled by TCP, don't confuse it */
5681 FALSE(0),
5682 &pdu_len);
5683 return pdu_len;
5684}

5686static gboolean
5687dissect_dcerpc_tcp(tvbuff_t *tvb, packet_info *pinfo, proto_tree *tree, void *data)
5688{
5689 dcerpc_decode_as_data* decode_data;
5690
5691 if (!is_dcerpc(tvb, 0, pinfo))
5692 return 0;
5693
5694 decode_data = dcerpc_get_decode_data(pinfo);
5695 decode_data->dcetransporttype = DCE_TRANSPORT_UNKNOWN0;
5696
5697 tcp_dissect_pdus(tvb, pinfo, tree, dcerpc_cn_desegment, 10, get_dcerpc_pdu_len, dissect_dcerpc_pdu, data);
5698 return TRUE(!(0));
5699}

5720
5721static void
5722dissect_dcerpc_dg_auth(tvbuff_t *tvb, int offset, proto_tree *dcerpc_tree,
5723 e_dce_dg_common_hdr_t *hdr, int *auth_level_p)
5724{
5725 proto_tree *auth_tree = NULL((void*)0);
5726 guint8 protection_level;
5727
5728 /*
5729 * Initially set "*auth_level_p" to -1 to indicate that we haven't
5730 * yet seen any authentication level information.
5731 */
5732 if (auth_level_p != NULL((void*)0))
5733 *auth_level_p = -1;
5734
5735 /*
5736 * The authentication information is at the *end* of the PDU; in
5737 * request and response PDUs, the request and response stub data
5738 * come before it.
5739 *
5740 * If the full packet is here, and there's data past the end of the
5741 * packet body, then dissect the auth info.
5742 */
5743 offset += hdr->frag_len;
5744 if (tvb_reported_length_remaining(tvb, offset) > 0) {
5745 switch (hdr->auth_proto) {
5746
5747 case DCE_C_RPC_AUTHN_PROTOCOL_KRB51:
5748 auth_tree = proto_tree_add_subtree(dcerpc_tree, tvb, offset, -1, ett_dcerpc_krb5_auth_verf, NULL((void*)0), "Kerberos authentication verifier");
5749 protection_level = tvb_get_guint8(tvb, offset);
5750 if (auth_level_p != NULL((void*)0))
5751 *auth_level_p = protection_level;
5752 proto_tree_add_uint(auth_tree, hf_dcerpc_krb5_av_prot_level, tvb, offset, 1, protection_level);
5753 offset++;
5754 proto_tree_add_item(auth_tree, hf_dcerpc_krb5_av_key_vers_num, tvb, offset, 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
5755 offset++;
5756 if (protection_level == DCE_C_AUTHN_LEVEL_PKT_PRIVACY6)
5757 offset += 6; /* 6 bytes of padding */
5758 else
5759 offset += 2; /* 2 bytes of padding */
5760 proto_tree_add_item(auth_tree, hf_dcerpc_krb5_av_key_auth_verifier, tvb, offset, 16, ENC_NA0x00000000);
5761 /*offset += 16;*/
5762 break;
5763
5764 default:
5765 proto_tree_add_item(dcerpc_tree, hf_dcerpc_authentication_verifier, tvb, offset, -1, ENC_NA0x00000000);
5766 break;
5767 }
5768 }
5769}
5770
5771static void
5772dissect_dcerpc_dg_cancel_ack(tvbuff_t *tvb, int offset, packet_info *pinfo,
5773 proto_tree *dcerpc_tree,
5774 e_dce_dg_common_hdr_t *hdr)
5775{
5776 guint32 version;
5777
5778 offset = dissect_dcerpc_uint32(tvb, offset, pinfo, dcerpc_tree,
5779 hdr->drep, hf_dcerpc_dg_cancel_vers,
5780 &version);
5781
5782 switch (version) {
5783
5784 case 0:
5785 /* The only version we know about */
5786 offset = dissect_dcerpc_uint32(tvb, offset, pinfo, dcerpc_tree,
5787 hdr->drep, hf_dcerpc_dg_cancel_id,
5788 NULL((void*)0));
5789 /*offset = */dissect_dcerpc_uint8(tvb, offset, pinfo, dcerpc_tree,
5790 hdr->drep, hf_dcerpc_dg_server_accepting_cancels,
5791 NULL((void*)0));
5792 break;
5793 }
5794}

5804 hdr->drep, hf_dcerpc_dg_cancel_vers,
5805 &version);
5806
5807 switch (version) {
5808
5809 case 0:
5810 /* The only version we know about */
5811 /*offset = */dissect_dcerpc_uint32(tvb, offset, pinfo, dcerpc_tree,
5812 hdr->drep, hf_dcerpc_dg_cancel_id,
5813 NULL((void*)0));
5814 /* XXX - are NDR Booleans 32 bits? */
5815

5817 the accepting_cancels field (it's only in the cancel_ack PDU)! */
5818 /*offset = dissect_dcerpc_uint32 (tvb, offset, pinfo, dcerpc_tree,

5821 break;

5824
5825static void
5826dissect_dcerpc_dg_fack(tvbuff_t *tvb, int offset, packet_info *pinfo,
5827 proto_tree *dcerpc_tree,
5828 e_dce_dg_common_hdr_t *hdr)
5829{
5830 guint8 version;
5831 guint16 serial_num;
5832 guint16 selack_len;
5833 guint i;
5834
5835 offset = dissect_dcerpc_uint8(tvb, offset, pinfo, dcerpc_tree,
5836 hdr->drep, hf_dcerpc_dg_fack_vers,
5837 &version);
5838 /* padding */
5839 offset++;
5840
5841 switch (version) {
5842
5843 case 0: /* The only version documented in the DCE RPC 1.1 spec */
5844 case 1: /* This appears to be the same */
5845 offset = dissect_dcerpc_uint16(tvb, offset, pinfo, dcerpc_tree,
5846 hdr->drep, hf_dcerpc_dg_fack_window_size,
5847 NULL((void*)0));
5848 offset = dissect_dcerpc_uint32(tvb, offset, pinfo, dcerpc_tree,
5849 hdr->drep, hf_dcerpc_dg_fack_max_tsdu,
5850 NULL((void*)0));
5851 offset = dissect_dcerpc_uint32(tvb, offset, pinfo, dcerpc_tree,
5852 hdr->drep, hf_dcerpc_dg_fack_max_frag_size,
5853 NULL((void*)0));
5854 offset = dissect_dcerpc_uint16(tvb, offset, pinfo, dcerpc_tree,
5855 hdr->drep, hf_dcerpc_dg_fack_serial_num,
5856 &serial_num);
5857 col_append_fstr(pinfo->cinfo, COL_INFO, " serial: %u",
5858 serial_num);
5859 offset = dissect_dcerpc_uint16(tvb, offset, pinfo, dcerpc_tree,
5860 hdr->drep, hf_dcerpc_dg_fack_selack_len,
5861 &selack_len);
5862 for (i = 0; i < selack_len; i++) {
5863 offset = dissect_dcerpc_uint32(tvb, offset, pinfo, dcerpc_tree,
5864 hdr->drep, hf_dcerpc_dg_fack_selack,
5865 NULL((void*)0));
5866 }
5867
5868 break;
5869 }
5870}

5872static void
5873dissect_dcerpc_dg_reject_fault(tvbuff_t *tvb, int offset, packet_info *pinfo,
5874 proto_tree *dcerpc_tree,

5887
5888static void
5889dissect_dcerpc_dg_stub(tvbuff_t *tvb, int offset, packet_info *pinfo,
5890 proto_tree *dcerpc_tree, proto_tree *tree,
5891 e_dce_dg_common_hdr_t *hdr, dcerpc_info *di)
5892{
5893 int length, reported_length, stub_length;
5894 gboolean save_fragmented;
5895 fragment_head *fd_head;
5896 tvbuff_t *next_tvb;
5897 proto_item *pi;
5898 proto_item *parent_pi;
5899
5900 col_append_fstr(pinfo->cinfo, COL_INFO, " opnum: %u len: %u",
5901 di->call_data->opnum, hdr->frag_len );
5902
5903 length = tvb_reported_length_remaining(tvb, offset);
5904 reported_length = tvb_reported_length_remaining(tvb, offset);
5905 stub_length = hdr->frag_len;
5906 if (length > stub_length)
5907 length = stub_length;
5908 if (reported_length > stub_length)
5909 reported_length = stub_length;
5910
5911 save_fragmented = pinfo->fragmented;
5912
5913 /* If we don't have reassembly enabled, or this packet contains
5914 the entire PDU, or if this is a short frame (or a frame
5915 not reassembled at a lower layer) that doesn't include all
5916 the data in the fragment, just call the handoff directly if
5917 this is the first fragment or the PDU isn't fragmented. */
5918 if ( (!dcerpc_reassemble) || !(hdr->flags1 & PFCL1_FRAG0x04) ||
5919 !tvb_bytes_exist(tvb, offset, stub_length) ) {
5920 if (hdr->frag_num == 0) {
5921
5922
5923 /* First fragment, possibly the only fragment */
5924
5925 /*
5926 * XXX - authentication info?
5927 */
5928 pinfo->fragmented = (hdr->flags1 & PFCL1_FRAG0x04);
5929 next_tvb = tvb_new_subset(tvb, offset, length,
5930 reported_length);
5931 dcerpc_try_handoff(pinfo, tree, dcerpc_tree, next_tvb, TRUE(!(0)), hdr->drep, di, NULL((void*)0));
5932 } else {
5933 /* PDU is fragmented and this isn't the first fragment */
5934 if (length > 0) {
5935 proto_tree_add_item(dcerpc_tree, hf_dcerpc_fragment_data, tvb, offset, stub_length, ENC_NA0x00000000);
5936 }
5937 }
5938 } else {
5939 /* Reassembly is enabled, the PDU is fragmented, and
5940 we have all the data in the fragment; the first two
5941 of those mean we should attempt reassembly, and the
5942 third means we can attempt reassembly. */
5943 if (length > 0) {
5944 proto_tree_add_item(dcerpc_tree, hf_dcerpc_fragment_data, tvb, offset, stub_length, ENC_NA0x00000000);
5945 }
5946
5947 fd_head = fragment_add_seq(&dcerpc_cl_reassembly_table,
5948 tvb, offset,
5949 pinfo, hdr->seqnum, (void *)hdr,
5950 hdr->frag_num, stub_length,
5951 !(hdr->flags1 & PFCL1_LASTFRAG0x02), 0);
5952 if (fd_head != NULL((void*)0)) {
5953 /* We completed reassembly... */
5954 if (pinfo->num == fd_head->reassembled_in) {
5955 /* ...and this is the reassembled RPC PDU */
5956 next_tvb = tvb_new_chain(tvb, fd_head->tvb_data);
5957 add_new_data_source(pinfo, next_tvb, "Reassembled DCE/RPC");
5958 show_fragment_seq_tree(fd_head, &dcerpc_frag_items,
5959 tree, pinfo, next_tvb, &pi);
5960
5961 /*
5962 * XXX - authentication info?
5963 */
5964 pinfo->fragmented = FALSE(0);
5965 dcerpc_try_handoff(pinfo, tree, dcerpc_tree, next_tvb, TRUE(!(0)), hdr->drep, di, NULL((void*)0));
5966 } else {
5967 /* ...and this isn't the reassembled RPC PDU */
5968 pi = proto_tree_add_uint(dcerpc_tree, hf_dcerpc_reassembled_in,
5969 tvb, 0, 0, fd_head->reassembled_in);
5970 PROTO_ITEM_SET_GENERATED(pi)do { if (pi) do { if (((pi)->finfo)) (((pi)->finfo))->
flags = (((pi)->finfo))->flags | (0x00000002); } while(
0); } while(0);
5971 parent_pi = proto_tree_get_parent(dcerpc_tree);
5972 if (parent_pi != NULL((void*)0)) {
5973 proto_item_append_text(parent_pi, ", [Reas: #%u]", fd_head->reassembled_in);
5974 }
5975 col_append_fstr(pinfo->cinfo, COL_INFO,
5976 " [DCE/RPC fragment, reas: #%u]", fd_head->reassembled_in);
5977 }
5978 }
5979 }
5980 pinfo->fragmented = save_fragmented;
5981}
5982
5983static void
5984dissect_dcerpc_dg_rqst(tvbuff_t *tvb, int offset, packet_info *pinfo,
5985 proto_tree *dcerpc_tree, proto_tree *tree,
5986 e_dce_dg_common_hdr_t *hdr, conversation_t *conv)
5987{
5988 dcerpc_info *di;
5989 dcerpc_call_value *value;
5990 dcerpc_matched_key matched_key, *new_matched_key;
5991 proto_item *pi;
5992 proto_item *parent_pi;
5993
5994 if (!(pinfo->fd->flags.visited)) {
5995 dcerpc_call_value *call_value;
5996 dcerpc_dg_call_key *call_key;
5997
5998 call_key = (dcerpc_dg_call_key *)wmem_alloc(wmem_file_scope(), sizeof (dcerpc_dg_call_key));
5999 call_key->conv = conv;
6000 call_key->seqnum = hdr->seqnum;
6001 call_key->act_id = hdr->act_id;
6002
6003 call_value = (dcerpc_call_value *)wmem_alloc(wmem_file_scope(), sizeof (dcerpc_call_value));
6004 call_value->uuid = hdr->if_id;
6005 call_value->ver = hdr->if_ver;
6006 call_value->object_uuid = hdr->obj_id;
6007 call_value->opnum = hdr->opnum;
6008 call_value->req_frame = pinfo->num;
6009 call_value->req_time = pinfo->abs_ts;
6010 call_value->rep_frame = 0;
6011 call_value->max_ptr = 0;
6012 call_value->se_data = NULL((void*)0);
6013 call_value->private_data = NULL((void*)0);
6014 call_value->pol = NULL((void*)0);
6015 /* NDR64 is not available on dg transports ?*/
6016 call_value->flags = 0;
6017
6018 g_hash_table_insert(dcerpc_dg_calls, call_key, call_value);
6019
6020 new_matched_key = (dcerpc_matched_key *)wmem_alloc(wmem_file_scope(), sizeof(dcerpc_matched_key));
6021 new_matched_key->frame = pinfo->num;
6022 new_matched_key->call_id = hdr->seqnum;
6023 g_hash_table_insert(dcerpc_matched, new_matched_key, call_value);
6024 }
6025
6026 matched_key.frame = pinfo->num;
6027 matched_key.call_id = hdr->seqnum;
6028 value = (dcerpc_call_value *)g_hash_table_lookup(dcerpc_matched, &matched_key);
6029 if (!value) {
6030 value = wmem_new(wmem_packet_scope(), dcerpc_call_value)((dcerpc_call_value*)wmem_alloc((wmem_packet_scope()), sizeof
(dcerpc_call_value)));
6031 value->uuid = hdr->if_id;
6032 value->ver = hdr->if_ver;
6033 value->object_uuid = hdr->obj_id;
6034 value->opnum = hdr->opnum;
6035 value->req_frame = pinfo->num;
6036 value->rep_frame = 0;
6037 value->max_ptr = 0;
6038 value->se_data = NULL((void*)0);
6039 value->private_data = NULL((void*)0);
6040 }
6041
6042 di = wmem_new0(wmem_packet_scope(), dcerpc_info)((dcerpc_info*)wmem_alloc0((wmem_packet_scope()), sizeof(dcerpc_info
)));
6043 di->dcerpc_procedure_name = "";
6044 di->conv = conv;
6045 di->call_id = hdr->seqnum;
6046 di->transport_salt = -1;
6047 di->ptype = PDU_REQ0;
6048 di->call_data = value;
6049
6050 if (value->rep_frame != 0) {
6051 pi = proto_tree_add_uint(dcerpc_tree, hf_dcerpc_response_in,
6052 tvb, 0, 0, value->rep_frame);
6053 PROTO_ITEM_SET_GENERATED(pi)do { if (pi) do { if (((pi)->finfo)) (((pi)->finfo))->
flags = (((pi)->finfo))->flags | (0x00000002); } while(
0); } while(0);
6054 parent_pi = proto_tree_get_parent(dcerpc_tree);
6055 if (parent_pi != NULL((void*)0)) {
6056 proto_item_append_text(parent_pi, ", [Resp: #%u]", value->rep_frame);
6057 }
6058 }
6059 dissect_dcerpc_dg_stub(tvb, offset, pinfo, dcerpc_tree, tree, hdr, di);
6060}
6061
6062static void
6063dissect_dcerpc_dg_resp(tvbuff_t *tvb, int offset, packet_info *pinfo,
6064 proto_tree *dcerpc_tree, proto_tree *tree,
6065 e_dce_dg_common_hdr_t *hdr, conversation_t *conv)
6066{
6067 dcerpc_info *di;
6068 dcerpc_call_value *value;
6069 dcerpc_matched_key matched_key, *new_matched_key;
6070 proto_item *pi;
6071 proto_item *parent_pi;
6072
6073 if (!(pinfo->fd->flags.visited)) {
6074 dcerpc_call_value *call_value;
6075 dcerpc_dg_call_key call_key;
6076
6077 call_key.conv = conv;
6078 call_key.seqnum = hdr->seqnum;
6079 call_key.act_id = hdr->act_id;
6080
6081 if ((call_value = (dcerpc_call_value *)g_hash_table_lookup(dcerpc_dg_calls, &call_key))) {
6082 new_matched_key = (dcerpc_matched_key *)wmem_alloc(wmem_file_scope(), sizeof (dcerpc_matched_key));
6083 new_matched_key->frame = pinfo->num;
6084 new_matched_key->call_id = hdr->seqnum;
6085 g_hash_table_insert(dcerpc_matched, new_matched_key, call_value);
6086 if (call_value->rep_frame == 0) {
6087 call_value->rep_frame = pinfo->num;
6088 }
6089 }
6090 }
6091
6092 matched_key.frame = pinfo->num;
6093 matched_key.call_id = hdr->seqnum;
6094 value = (dcerpc_call_value *)g_hash_table_lookup(dcerpc_matched, &matched_key);
6095 if (!value) {
6096 value = wmem_new0(wmem_packet_scope(), dcerpc_call_value)((dcerpc_call_value*)wmem_alloc0((wmem_packet_scope()), sizeof
(dcerpc_call_value)));
6097 value->uuid = hdr->if_id;
6098 value->ver = hdr->if_ver;
6099 value->object_uuid = hdr->obj_id;
6100 value->opnum = hdr->opnum;
6101 value->rep_frame = pinfo->num;
6102 }
6103
6104 di = wmem_new0(wmem_packet_scope(), dcerpc_info)((dcerpc_info*)wmem_alloc0((wmem_packet_scope()), sizeof(dcerpc_info
)));
6105 di->dcerpc_procedure_name = "";
6106 di->conv = conv;
6107 di->transport_salt = -1;
6108 di->ptype = PDU_RESP2;
6109 di->call_data = value;
6110
6111 if (value->req_frame != 0) {
6112 nstime_t delta_ts;
6113 pi = proto_tree_add_uint(dcerpc_tree, hf_dcerpc_request_in,
6114 tvb, 0, 0, value->req_frame);
6115 PROTO_ITEM_SET_GENERATED(pi)do { if (pi) do { if (((pi)->finfo)) (((pi)->finfo))->
flags = (((pi)->finfo))->flags | (0x00000002); } while(
0); } while(0);
6116 parent_pi = proto_tree_get_parent(dcerpc_tree);
6117 if (parent_pi != NULL((void*)0)) {
6118 proto_item_append_text(parent_pi, ", [Req: #%u]", value->req_frame);
6119 }
6120 nstime_delta(&delta_ts, &pinfo->abs_ts, &value->req_time);
6121 pi = proto_tree_add_time(dcerpc_tree, hf_dcerpc_time, tvb, offset, 0, &delta_ts);
6122 PROTO_ITEM_SET_GENERATED(pi)do { if (pi) do { if (((pi)->finfo)) (((pi)->finfo))->
flags = (((pi)->finfo))->flags | (0x00000002); } while(
0); } while(0);
6123 } else {
6124 proto_tree_add_expert(dcerpc_tree, pinfo, &ei_dcerpc_no_request_found, tvb, 0, 0);
6125 }
6126 dissect_dcerpc_dg_stub(tvb, offset, pinfo, dcerpc_tree, tree, hdr, di);
6127}
6128
6129static void
6130dissect_dcerpc_dg_ping_ack(tvbuff_t *tvb, int offset, packet_info *pinfo,
6131 proto_tree *dcerpc_tree,
6132 e_dce_dg_common_hdr_t *hdr, conversation_t *conv)
6133{
6134 proto_item *parent_pi;
6135/* if (!(pinfo->fd->flags.visited)) {*/
6136 dcerpc_call_value *call_value;
6137 dcerpc_dg_call_key call_key;
6138
6139 call_key.conv = conv;
6140 call_key.seqnum = hdr->seqnum;
6141 call_key.act_id = hdr->act_id;
6142
6143 if ((call_value = (dcerpc_call_value *)g_hash_table_lookup(dcerpc_dg_calls, &call_key))) {
6144 proto_item *pi;
6145 nstime_t delta_ts;
6146
6147 pi = proto_tree_add_uint(dcerpc_tree, hf_dcerpc_request_in,
6148 tvb, 0, 0, call_value->req_frame);
6149 PROTO_ITEM_SET_GENERATED(pi)do { if (pi) do { if (((pi)->finfo)) (((pi)->finfo))->
flags = (((pi)->finfo))->flags | (0x00000002); } while(
0); } while(0);
6150 parent_pi = proto_tree_get_parent(dcerpc_tree);
6151 if (parent_pi != NULL((void*)0)) {
6152 proto_item_append_text(parent_pi, ", [Req: #%u]", call_value->req_frame);
6153 }
6154
6155 col_append_fstr(pinfo->cinfo, COL_INFO, " [req: #%u]", call_value->req_frame);
6156
6157 nstime_delta(&delta_ts, &pinfo->abs_ts, &call_value->req_time);
6158 pi = proto_tree_add_time(dcerpc_tree, hf_dcerpc_time, tvb, offset, 0, &delta_ts);
6159 PROTO_ITEM_SET_GENERATED(pi)do { if (pi) do { if (((pi)->finfo)) (((pi)->finfo))->
flags = (((pi)->finfo))->flags | (0x00000002); } while(
0); } while(0);
6160/* }*/
6161 }
6162}
6163
6164/*
6165 * DCERPC dissector for connectionless calls
6166 */
6167static gboolean
6168dissect_dcerpc_dg(tvbuff_t *tvb, packet_info *pinfo, proto_tree *tree, void *data _U___attribute__((unused)))
6169{
6170 proto_item *ti = NULL((void*)0);
6171 proto_tree *dcerpc_tree = NULL((void*)0);
6172 e_dce_dg_common_hdr_t hdr;
6173 int offset = 0;
6174 conversation_t *conv;
6175 int auth_level;
6176 char *uuid_str;
6177 const char *uuid_name = NULL((void*)0);
6178 static const int * hdr_flags1[] = {
6179 &hf_dcerpc_dg_flags1_rsrvd_80,
6180 &hf_dcerpc_dg_flags1_broadcast,
6181 &hf_dcerpc_dg_flags1_idempotent,
6182 &hf_dcerpc_dg_flags1_maybe,
6183 &hf_dcerpc_dg_flags1_nofack,
6184 &hf_dcerpc_dg_flags1_frag,
6185 &hf_dcerpc_dg_flags1_last_frag,
6186 &hf_dcerpc_dg_flags1_rsrvd_01,
6187 NULL((void*)0)
6188 };
6189
6190 static const int * hdr_flags2[] = {
6191 &hf_dcerpc_dg_flags2_rsrvd_80,
6192 &hf_dcerpc_dg_flags2_rsrvd_40,
6193 &hf_dcerpc_dg_flags2_rsrvd_20,
6194 &hf_dcerpc_dg_flags2_rsrvd_10,
6195 &hf_dcerpc_dg_flags2_rsrvd_08,
6196 &hf_dcerpc_dg_flags2_rsrvd_04,
6197 &hf_dcerpc_dg_flags2_cancel_pending,
6198 &hf_dcerpc_dg_flags2_rsrvd_01,
6199 NULL((void*)0)
6200 };
6201
6202 /*
6203 * Check if this looks like a CL DCERPC call. All dg packets
6204 * have an 80 byte header on them. Which starts with
6205 * version (4), pkt_type.
6206 */
6207 if (tvb_reported_length(tvb) < sizeof (hdr)) {
6208 return FALSE(0);
6209 }
6210
6211 /* Version must be 4 */
6212 hdr.rpc_ver = tvb_get_guint8(tvb, offset++);
6213 if (hdr.rpc_ver != 4)
6214 return FALSE(0);
6215
6216 /* Type must be <= 19 or it's not DCE/RPC */
6217 hdr.ptype = tvb_get_guint8(tvb, offset++);
6218 if (hdr.ptype > 19)
6219 return FALSE(0);
6220
6221 /* flags1 has bit 1 and 8 as reserved so if any of them are set, it is
6222 probably not a DCE/RPC packet
6223 */
6224 hdr.flags1 = tvb_get_guint8(tvb, offset++);
6225 if (hdr.flags1&0x81)
6226 return FALSE(0);
6227
6228 /* flags2 has all bits except bit 2 as reserved so if any of them are set
6229 it is probably not DCE/RPC.
6230 */
6231 hdr.flags2 = tvb_get_guint8(tvb, offset++);
6232 if (hdr.flags2&0xfd)
6233 return FALSE(0);
6234
6235
6236 col_set_str(pinfo->cinfo, COL_PROTOCOL, "DCERPC");
6237 col_add_str(pinfo->cinfo, COL_INFO, pckt_vals[hdr.ptype].strptr);
6238
6239 tvb_memcpy(tvb, (guint8 *)hdr.drep, offset, sizeof (hdr.drep));
6240 offset += (int)sizeof (hdr.drep);
6241 hdr.serial_hi = tvb_get_guint8(tvb, offset++);
6242 dcerpc_tvb_get_uuid(tvb, offset, hdr.drep, &hdr.obj_id);
6243 offset += 16;
6244 dcerpc_tvb_get_uuid(tvb, offset, hdr.drep, &hdr.if_id);
6245 offset += 16;
6246 dcerpc_tvb_get_uuid(tvb, offset, hdr.drep, &hdr.act_id);
6247 offset += 16;
6248 hdr.server_boot = dcerpc_tvb_get_ntohl(tvb, offset, hdr.drep);
6249 offset += 4;
6250 hdr.if_ver = dcerpc_tvb_get_ntohl(tvb, offset, hdr.drep);
6251 offset += 4;
6252 hdr.seqnum = dcerpc_tvb_get_ntohl(tvb, offset, hdr.drep);
6253 offset += 4;
6254 hdr.opnum = dcerpc_tvb_get_ntohs(tvb, offset, hdr.drep);
6255 offset += 2;
6256 hdr.ihint = dcerpc_tvb_get_ntohs(tvb, offset, hdr.drep);
6257 offset += 2;
6258 hdr.ahint = dcerpc_tvb_get_ntohs(tvb, offset, hdr.drep);
6259 offset += 2;
6260 hdr.frag_len = dcerpc_tvb_get_ntohs(tvb, offset, hdr.drep);
6261 offset += 2;
6262 hdr.frag_num = dcerpc_tvb_get_ntohs(tvb, offset, hdr.drep);
6263 offset += 2;
6264 hdr.auth_proto = tvb_get_guint8(tvb, offset++);
6265 hdr.serial_lo = tvb_get_guint8(tvb, offset++);
6266
6267 if (tree) {
6268 ti = proto_tree_add_item(tree, proto_dcerpc, tvb, 0, -1, ENC_NA0x00000000);
6269 if (ti) {
6270 dcerpc_tree = proto_item_add_subtree(ti, ett_dcerpc);
6271 proto_item_append_text(ti, " %s, Seq: %u, Serial: %u, Frag: %u, FragLen: %u",
6272 val_to_str(hdr.ptype, pckt_vals, "Unknown (0x%02x)"),
6273 hdr.seqnum, hdr.serial_hi*256+hdr.serial_lo,
6274 hdr.frag_num, hdr.frag_len);
6275 }
6276 }
6277 offset = 0;
6278
6279 proto_tree_add_uint(dcerpc_tree, hf_dcerpc_ver, tvb, offset, 1, hdr.rpc_ver);
6280 offset++;
6281
6282 proto_tree_add_uint(dcerpc_tree, hf_dcerpc_packet_type, tvb, offset, 1, hdr.ptype);
6283 offset++;
6284
6285 proto_tree_add_bitmask_value(dcerpc_tree, tvb, offset, hf_dcerpc_dg_flags1,
6286 ett_dcerpc_dg_flags1, hdr_flags1, hdr.flags1);
6287 offset++;
6288
6289 proto_tree_add_bitmask_value(dcerpc_tree, tvb, offset, hf_dcerpc_dg_flags2,
6290 ett_dcerpc_dg_flags2, hdr_flags2, hdr.flags2);
6291 offset++;
6292
6293 if (tree) {
6294 proto_tree_add_dcerpc_drep(dcerpc_tree, tvb, offset, hdr.drep, (int)sizeof (hdr.drep));
6295 }
6296 offset += (int)sizeof (hdr.drep);
6297
6298 if (tree)
6299 proto_tree_add_uint(dcerpc_tree, hf_dcerpc_dg_serial_hi, tvb, offset, 1, hdr.serial_hi);
6300 offset++;
6301
6302 if (tree) {
6303 proto_tree_add_guid_format(dcerpc_tree, hf_dcerpc_obj_id, tvb,
6304 offset, 16, (e_guid_t *) &hdr.obj_id, "Object UUID: %s",
6305 guid_to_str(wmem_packet_scope(), (e_guid_t *) &hdr.obj_id));
6306 }
6307 offset += 16;
6308
6309 if (tree) {
6310 uuid_str = guid_to_str(wmem_packet_scope(), (e_guid_t*)&hdr.if_id);
6311 uuid_name = guids_get_uuid_name(&hdr.if_id)guids_get_guid_name((e_guid_t *) (&hdr.if_id));
6312 if (uuid_name) {
6313 proto_tree_add_guid_format(dcerpc_tree, hf_dcerpc_dg_if_id, tvb,
6314 offset, 16, (e_guid_t *) &hdr.if_id, "Interface: %s UUID: %s", uuid_name, uuid_str);
6315 } else {
6316 proto_tree_add_guid_format(dcerpc_tree, hf_dcerpc_dg_if_id, tvb,
6317 offset, 16, (e_guid_t *) &hdr.if_id, "Interface UUID: %s", uuid_str);
6318 }
6319 }
6320 offset += 16;
6321
6322 if (tree) {
6323 proto_tree_add_guid_format(dcerpc_tree, hf_dcerpc_dg_act_id, tvb,
6324 offset, 16, (e_guid_t *) &hdr.act_id, "Activity: %s",
6325 guid_to_str(wmem_packet_scope(), (e_guid_t *) &hdr.act_id));
6326 }
6327 offset += 16;
6328
6329 if (tree) {
6330 nstime_t server_boot;
6331
6332 server_boot.secs = hdr.server_boot;
6333 server_boot.nsecs = 0;
6334
6335 if (hdr.server_boot == 0)
6336 proto_tree_add_time_format_value(dcerpc_tree, hf_dcerpc_dg_server_boot,
6337 tvb, offset, 4, &server_boot,
6338 "Unknown (0)");
6339 else
6340 proto_tree_add_time(dcerpc_tree, hf_dcerpc_dg_server_boot,
6341 tvb, offset, 4, &server_boot);
6342 }
6343 offset += 4;
6344
6345 if (tree)
6346 proto_tree_add_uint(dcerpc_tree, hf_dcerpc_dg_if_ver, tvb, offset, 4, hdr.if_ver);
6347 offset += 4;
6348
6349 if (tree)
6350 proto_tree_add_uint(dcerpc_tree, hf_dcerpc_dg_seqnum, tvb, offset, 4, hdr.seqnum);
6351 col_append_fstr(pinfo->cinfo, COL_INFO, ": seq: %u", hdr.seqnum);
6352 col_append_fstr(pinfo->cinfo, COL_DCE_CALL, "%u", hdr.seqnum);
6353 offset += 4;
6354
6355 if (tree)
6356 proto_tree_add_uint(dcerpc_tree, hf_dcerpc_opnum, tvb, offset, 2, hdr.opnum);
6357 offset += 2;
6358
6359 if (tree)
6360 proto_tree_add_uint(dcerpc_tree, hf_dcerpc_dg_ihint, tvb, offset, 2, hdr.ihint);
6361 offset += 2;
6362
6363 if (tree)
6364 proto_tree_add_uint(dcerpc_tree, hf_dcerpc_dg_ahint, tvb, offset, 2, hdr.ahint);
6365 offset += 2;
6366
6367 if (tree)
6368 proto_tree_add_uint(dcerpc_tree, hf_dcerpc_dg_frag_len, tvb, offset, 2, hdr.frag_len);
6369 offset += 2;
6370
6371 if (tree)
6372 proto_tree_add_uint(dcerpc_tree, hf_dcerpc_dg_frag_num, tvb, offset, 2, hdr.frag_num);
6373 if (hdr.flags1 & PFCL1_FRAG0x04) {
6374 /* Fragmented - put the fragment number into the Info column */
6375 col_append_fstr(pinfo->cinfo, COL_INFO, " frag: %u",
6376 hdr.frag_num);
6377 }
6378 offset += 2;
6379
6380 if (tree)
6381 proto_tree_add_uint(dcerpc_tree, hf_dcerpc_dg_auth_proto, tvb, offset, 1, hdr.auth_proto);
6382 offset++;
6383
6384 if (tree)
6385 proto_tree_add_uint(dcerpc_tree, hf_dcerpc_dg_serial_lo, tvb, offset, 1, hdr.serial_lo);
6386 if (hdr.flags1 & PFCL1_FRAG0x04) {
6387 /* Fragmented - put the serial number into the Info column */
6388 col_append_fstr(pinfo->cinfo, COL_INFO, " serial: %u",
6389 (hdr.serial_hi << 8) | hdr.serial_lo);
6390 }
6391 offset++;
6392
6393 if (tree) {
6394 /*
6395 * XXX - for Kerberos, we get a protection level; if it's
6396 * DCE_C_AUTHN_LEVEL_PKT_PRIVACY, we can't dissect the
6397 * stub data.
6398 */
6399 dissect_dcerpc_dg_auth(tvb, offset, dcerpc_tree, &hdr,
6400 &auth_level);
6401 }
6402
6403 /*
6404 * keeping track of the conversation shouldn't really be necessary
6405 * for connectionless packets, because everything we need to know
6406 * to dissect is in the header for each packet. Unfortunately,
6407 * Microsoft's implementation is buggy and often puts the
6408 * completely wrong if_id in the header. go figure. So, keep
6409 * track of the seqnum and use that if possible. Note: that's not
6410 * completely correct. It should really be done based on both the
6411 * activity_id and seqnum. I haven't seen anywhere that it would
6412 * make a difference, but for future reference...
6413 */
6414 conv = find_or_create_conversation(pinfo);
6415
6416 /*
6417 * Packet type specific stuff is next.
6418 */
6419
6420 switch (hdr.ptype) {
6421
6422 case PDU_CANCEL_ACK10:
6423 /* Body is optional */
6424 /* XXX - we assume "frag_len" is the length of the body */
6425 if (hdr.frag_len != 0)
6426 dissect_dcerpc_dg_cancel_ack(tvb, offset, pinfo, dcerpc_tree, &hdr);
6427 break;
6428
6429 case PDU_CL_CANCEL8:
6430 /*
6431 * XXX - The DCE RPC 1.1 spec doesn't say the body is optional,
6432 * but in at least one capture none of the Cl_cancel PDUs had a
6433 * body.
6434 */
6435 /* XXX - we assume "frag_len" is the length of the body */
6436 if (hdr.frag_len != 0)
6437 dissect_dcerpc_dg_cancel(tvb, offset, pinfo, dcerpc_tree, &hdr);
6438 break;
6439
6440 case PDU_NOCALL5:
6441 /* Body is optional; if present, it's the same as PDU_FACK */
6442 /* XXX - we assume "frag_len" is the length of the body */
6443 if (hdr.frag_len != 0)
6444 dissect_dcerpc_dg_fack(tvb, offset, pinfo, dcerpc_tree, &hdr);
6445 break;
6446
6447 case PDU_FACK9:
6448 /* Body is optional */
6449 /* XXX - we assume "frag_len" is the length of the body */
6450 if (hdr.frag_len != 0)
6451 dissect_dcerpc_dg_fack(tvb, offset, pinfo, dcerpc_tree, &hdr);
6452 break;
6453
6454 case PDU_REJECT6:
6455 case PDU_FAULT3:
6456 dissect_dcerpc_dg_reject_fault(tvb, offset, pinfo, dcerpc_tree, &hdr);
6457 break;
6458
6459 case PDU_REQ0:
6460 dissect_dcerpc_dg_rqst(tvb, offset, pinfo, dcerpc_tree, tree, &hdr, conv);
6461 break;
6462
6463 case PDU_RESP2:
6464 dissect_dcerpc_dg_resp(tvb, offset, pinfo, dcerpc_tree, tree, &hdr, conv);
6465 break;
6466
6467 /* these requests have no body */
6468 case PDU_ACK7:
6469 case PDU_PING1:
6470 dissect_dcerpc_dg_ping_ack(tvb, offset, pinfo, dcerpc_tree, &hdr, conv);
6471 break;
6472 case PDU_WORKING4:
6473 default:
6474 break;
6475 }
6476
6477 return TRUE(!(0));
6478}
6479
6480static void
6481dcerpc_init_protocol(void)
6482{
6483 /* structures and data for BIND */
6484 dcerpc_binds = g_hash_table_new(dcerpc_bind_hash, dcerpc_bind_equal);
6485
6486 /* structures and data for CALL */
6487 dcerpc_cn_calls = g_hash_table_new(dcerpc_cn_call_hash, dcerpc_cn_call_equal);
6488 dcerpc_dg_calls = g_hash_table_new(dcerpc_dg_call_hash, dcerpc_dg_call_equal);
6489
6490 /* structure and data for MATCHED */
6491 dcerpc_matched = g_hash_table_new(dcerpc_matched_hash, dcerpc_matched_equal);
6492 decode_dcerpc_inject_bindings();
6493}
6494
6495static void
6496dcerpc_cleanup_protocol(void)
6497{
6498 g_hash_table_destroy(dcerpc_binds);
6499 g_hash_table_destroy(dcerpc_cn_calls);
6500 g_hash_table_destroy(dcerpc_dg_calls);
6501 g_hash_table_destroy(dcerpc_matched);
6502}

6947 expert_register_field_array(expert_dcerpc, ei, array_length(ei)(sizeof ei / sizeof ei[0]));

6950
6951 register_init_routine(dcerpc_init_protocol);
6952 register_cleanup_routine(dcerpc_cleanup_protocol);
6953 dcerpc_module = prefs_register_protocol(proto_dcerpc, NULL((void*)0));
6954 prefs_register_bool_preference(dcerpc_module,
6955 "desegment_dcerpc",
6956 "Reassemble DCE/RPC messages spanning multiple TCP segments",
6957 "Whether the DCE/RPC dissector should reassemble messages"
6958 " spanning multiple TCP segments."
6959 " To use this option, you must also enable"
6960 " \"Allow subdissectors to reassemble TCP streams\" in the TCP protocol settings.",
6961 &dcerpc_cn_desegment);
6962 prefs_register_bool_preference(dcerpc_module,
6963 "reassemble_dcerpc",
6964 "Reassemble DCE/RPC fragments",
6965 "Whether the DCE/RPC dissector should reassemble fragmented DCE/RPC PDUs",
6966 &dcerpc_reassemble);
6967 register_init_routine(dcerpc_reassemble_init);
6968 dcerpc_uuids = g_hash_table_new(dcerpc_uuid_hash, dcerpc_uuid_equal);
6969 dcerpc_tap = register_tap("dcerpc");
6970

6980void
6981proto_reg_handoff_dcerpc(void)
6982{
6983 heur_dissector_add("tcp", dissect_dcerpc_tcp, "DCE/RPC over TCP", "dcerpc_tcp", proto_dcerpc, HEURISTIC_ENABLE);
6984 heur_dissector_add("netbios", dissect_dcerpc_cn_pk, "DCE/RPC over NetBios", "dcerpc_netbios", proto_dcerpc, HEURISTIC_ENABLE);
6985 heur_dissector_add("udp", dissect_dcerpc_dg, "DCE/RPC over UDP", "dcerpc_udp", proto_dcerpc, HEURISTIC_ENABLE);
6986 heur_dissector_add("smb_transact", dissect_dcerpc_cn_smbpipe, "DCE/RPC over SMB", "dcerpc_smb_transact", proto_dcerpc, HEURISTIC_ENABLE);
6987 heur_dissector_add("smb2_pipe_subdissectors", dissect_dcerpc_cn_smb2, "DCE/RPC over SMB2", "dcerpc_smb2", proto_dcerpc, HEURISTIC_ENABLE);
6988 heur_dissector_add("http", dissect_dcerpc_cn_bs, "DCE/RPC over HTTP", "dcerpc_http", proto_dcerpc, HEURISTIC_ENABLE);
6989 dcerpc_smb_init(proto_dcerpc);
6990
6991 guids_add_uuid(&uuid_data_repr_proto, "32bit NDR")guids_add_guid((const e_guid_t *) (&uuid_data_repr_proto)
, ("32bit NDR"));
6992 guids_add_uuid(&uuid_ndr64, "64bit NDR")guids_add_guid((const e_guid_t *) (&uuid_ndr64), ("64bit NDR"
));
6993 guids_add_uuid(&uuid_asyncemsmdb, "async MAPI")guids_add_guid((const e_guid_t *) (&uuid_asyncemsmdb), ("async MAPI"
));
6994}
